<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="11" pageNumber="40" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,957,2035]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,352,1181,1207]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">Description:</emphasis>
Measurements are of a 
<typeStatus box="[636,737,1181,1207]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">paratype</typeStatus>
male, followed by those of a 
<typeStatus box="[1089,1190,1181,1207]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">paratype</typeStatus>
female within round brackets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,957,2035]" box="[198,831,1256,1282]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">Body length 3.35 (3.80); maximum width 1.20 (1.40).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,957,2035]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">Coloration: Generally black, with apex of tylus, a small median basal spot on head, most of posterior half of pronotum particularly laterally and, in the middle, broad lateral (outer 1/2 to 2/3 width) areas of clavus and corium, and narrow outer areas of membrane, contrastingly pale. Coxae black except at apex, femora black with base and apex testaceous, tibiae and tarsi testaceous with bases and apices fuscous, other details as in original description.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,957,2035]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">
Structure: Head rugosely punctae and densely clothed with short white pubescence. Length of head 0.74 (0.80); width across eyes 1.00 (1.10); interocular space 0.60 (0.60); interocellar space 0.29 (0.30); eye-ocellar space 0.11(0.11); eye length 0.30 (0.30); eye width 0.20 (0.20). Labium extending to hind coxae, 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1319,1330,1555,1569]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">st</superScript>
segment reaching base of head, length of segments: I 0.53 (0.60); II 0.53 (0.57); III 0.45 (0.40); IV 0.41 (0.38). Antennae with 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[347,360,1632,1646]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">rd</superScript>
and 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[434,446,1632,1646]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">th</superScript>
segments subequal in length, length of segments: I 0.30 (0.34); II 0.0.60 (0.53); III 0.55 (0.68); IV 0.64 (0.68).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,957,2035]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">Thorax: Pronotum very coarsely punctae with a central impression, and clothed with white decumbent pubescence anteriorly; median length 0.70 (0.76); width at anterior margin 0.65 (0.80); width at posterior margin 1.14 (1.30). Scutellum very coarsely punctae and clothed with decumbent white pubescence; length 0.57 (0.60); width 0.68 (0.70). Length of hemelytra 2.60 (2.66); length of corium 1.78 (1.82); claval commissure 0.38 (0.38), corium clothed with sparse non-decumbent setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,957,2035]" box="[198,861,1897,1923]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">
Abdomen: All genitalia details generally as in 
<emphasis box="[744,861,1897,1922]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName box="[744,858,1897,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Nysius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vinitor">N. vinitor</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,957,2035]" box="[198,966,1934,1960]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">
Male: Pygophore, paramere, and aedeagus details as in 
<emphasis box="[849,966,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName box="[849,962,1934,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" genus="Nysius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vinitor">N. vinitor</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,957,2035]" pageId="11" pageNumber="40">Female: Spermatheca short, 2–3 twisted, not quite coiled; apical sac part slightly narrower than subapical part.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,152,402]" box="[198,654,152,178]" pageId="12" pageNumber="41">Other details as in original description.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
